I need to identify the line item in the cash flow statement that represents the amount of profit after all expenses have been deducted from revenue.

Looking at the cash flow statement, the "Net Profit" line item under "Cash Flow From Operating Activities" represents the profit that an entity retains after all expenses have been deducted. This is the bottom-line profit figure after accounting for operating costs, interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization.

From the statement, I can see that the Net Profit amount is -1342040.76 on 2024-01-28.

Therefore, the value that represents the profit after all expenses is -1342040.76.

{"solution": {'value': '-1342040.76'}}
